Oeta, Cato of Utica, and Cleopatra, . . . what suicides do you see in the paintings 
of the old masters?" Ch. B., Oeuures, vol. 2, pp. 133-134. 119 Suicide appears, then, 
as the quintessence of modernity. [ J74a,2] 

