The city made of markets. Thus Riga, when viewed from the other side of the 
river in the evening light, looks like a warehouse. When multicolored clouds 
gather over the ocean, Chinese legend says the gods are coming together to hold 
a market. They name this phenomenon hai-thi, or the sea-market. <F°, 1 > 

Comparison of the arcades to the indoor arenas in which one learned to ride a bicycle. In 
these halls the figure of the woman assumed its most seductive aspect: as cyclist. That is 
how she appears on contemporary posters. Cheret as painter of this feminine pulchritude. 
