the invasion of the letters. <F°,22> 

The structure of books like La Grande Ville, Le Diable a Paris, Les Frangau peinls par 
eux-memes is a literary phenomenon that corresponds to the stereoscopes, panoramas, and 
so fordi. <See Q2,6.> <F°,23> 

The true has no windows. Nowhere does the true look out to the universe. And the 
interest of the panorama is in seeing the true city. "The city in the bottle" — the city 
indoors. What is found within the windowless house is the true. One such windowless 
house is the theater; hence the eternal pleasure it affords. Hence, also, the pleasure taken 
in those windowless rotundas, the panoramas. In the theater, after the beginning of the 
performance, the doors remain closed. Those passing through arcades are, in a certain 
sense, inhabitants of a panorama. The windows of this house open out on them. They can 
be seen out these windows but cannot themselves look in. <See Q2a,7> <F°,24> 

