entitled "Fashion's Revenge on the Flowers." Grandville's works are the sibylline books of 
publicite. Everything that, with him, has its preliminary form as joke, or satire, attains its 
true unfolding as advertisement. <See B4,5 and Gl,3.> <M°,3> 



