Task of childhood: to bring the new world into symbolic space <Symbolraum>. The child, 
in fact, can do what the grownup absolutely cannot: remember the new once again. For 
us, locomotives already have symbolic character because we met with them in childhood. 
Our children, however, will find this in automobiles, of which we ourselves see only the 
new, elegant, modern, cheeky side. <See Kla,3.> <M°,20> 

