Title of a painting by Wiertz: Les Choses du present devant les hommes de I'avenir 
<The Things of the Present on Display before the Men of the Future>. Note- 
worthy is the tendency of this painter toward allegory. For example, in the 
catalogue description of the picture Une Second apres la mort, we read: "Consider 
die idea of a book that has fallen from one's hands, and on its cover these words: 
Lofty Achievements of Humanity." Oeuvres littemires, p. 496. Figure of "civilization" 
and many other allegories in Le Dernier Canon. <0°,21> 

