with the intention of proving the necessity of having women trained in the use of 
firearms. It was Monsieur Wiertz, as we know, who had the idea of setting up a 
special rifle range for ladies and offering, as prize in the competition, a portrait of 
the victorious heroine." Oeuvres litteraires, p. 501 (catalogue of works, edited by 



