One can characterize the problem of the form of the new art straight on: When and how 
will the worlds of form wliich, without our having expected it, have arisen, for example, 
in mechanics, or in machine construction, and subjugated us — when will they make 
whatever nature they contain into primal history? When will we reach a state of society in 
<which these forms, or> those arising from them, <reveal> themselves to us as natural 
forms? <See K3a,2.) <0°,32> 

