U [Saint-Simon, Railroads] 

1. Ateliers nationaux: an emergency relief agency, set up during the February Revolution 
of 1848, that attracted thousands of unemployed workers from all over France; it 
eventually satisfied neither radicals nor moderates and was abolished by the newly 
elected conservative majority in May, without any program of public works to replace 
it. 

