9, Saint-Simon married the young writer and musician Sophie de Champgrand in Au- 
gust 1801; having just assumed the role of patron of the sciences, he was in need of a 
hostess. The marriage was dissolved, by mutual consent, in June 1802. "I used 
marriage as a means of studying scientists" (Selected Writings on Science, Industry and 
Social Organization, p. 19). 

10. Auguste Comte became Saint-Simon's assistant in 1817, following his expulsion from 
the Ecole Polytechnique for insubordination. It was in 1824 — after seven years of 
collaboration — that a long-standing dispute between the two men finally led Comte 
to withdraw his support. 

