10. After the victory at Sedan and the capture of Napoleon III, on September 1, 1870, 
Prussian forces advanced on Paris and, by September 23, had surrounded the city. 



The siege lasted until the end of January, when an armistice was signed, ending the 
Franco-Prussian War. 

11. In the course of "Bloody Week" (May 21-28, 1871), the Communards resisted 
Thiers's forces street by street, retreating toward the heart of Paris. In their despera- 
tion, they executed a number of hostages, including the archbishop of Paris. 

12. At issue is Thiers's art collection. 

