trans. MatthewJ. O'Connell (New York: Continuum, 1995), pp. 234-236; and idem, 
"Remarks on Philosopliical Anthropology," in Horkheimer, Between Philosophy and 
Social Science, trans. G. Frederick Hunter, Matthew S. Kramer, and John Torpey 
(Cambridge, Mass.: MIT Press, 1993), p. 664. 

7. ". . . der gelaufigen Erfahrung den Erlebnischarakter abzumerken." In the sentence 
following, "the experience" translates die Erfahrung. 

