lish, "The Storyteller," in Illuminations, trans. Harry Zohn (New York: Schocken, 
1969), pp. 91-92, 92-93 (section 9). 

10. Literally, "gilded youth," fashionable and wealthy young people; specifically, in 
France, the fashionable set of the reactionary party in 1794. 



